    "Maryland was chosen for several reasons:",
    "Maryland contains roughly 5% of the total patients in the dataset (2,358,928). 2.",
    "Our dataset has a slight Midwestern bias, and Maryland is geographically separated from the Midwest. 3.",
    "Maryland varies demographically from the dataset overall, with a higher African American population and a lower white population. 4.",
    "In our dataset, there is less data available per patient in Maryland (average record length 287) than in the rest of the population (average record length 521), making patients more difficult to classify."
